{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "trade-license-workflow-v1",
    "name": "Trade License Workflow API",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Trade License workflow.\n\n**Required headers per role:**\n| Role | X-Role | X-User-ID |\n|------|--------|-----------|\n| Customer | CUSTOMER | {{customer_id}} |\n| Reviewer | REVIEWER | {{reviewer_id}} |\n| Approver | APPROVER | {{approver_id}} |\n\n**Workflow order:**\n1. Customer submits → SUBMITTED\n2. Reviewer accepts/rejects/adjusts → ACCEPTED | REJECTED | ADJUSTED\n3. Approver approves/rejects/rereview → APPROVED | REJECTED | REREVIEW\n\n**Quick start:**\n1. Import the companion environment file `trade-license.postman_environment.json`\n2. Select the `Trade License - Local` environment\n3. Run requests top-to-bottom — Submit auto-saves `{{app_id}}`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status field is ok', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Liveness check. No authentication required."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["health"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Customer",
      "description": "Use Case: Applicant requests new application for Trade License.\nAll requests require `X-Role: CUSTOMER` and `X-User-ID` headers.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit Application (Steps 1–4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate a unique transaction ID on every run to avoid duplicate key errors",
                  "const txnId = 'TXN-' + pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$randomUUID}}');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('txn_id', txnId);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Returns application_id', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.application_id).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    // Auto-save for use in all subsequent requests",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('app_id', json.application_id);",
                  "    console.log('Saved app_id:', json.application_id);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "CUSTOMER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{customer_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"license_type\": \"TRADE_LICENSE\",\n  \"commodity\": {\n    \"name\": \"General Trading\",\n    \"description\": \"Import and export of consumer goods\",\n    \"category\": \"Commerce\"\n  },\n  \"documents\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Passport Copy\",\n      \"url\": \"https://storage.example.com/docs/passport.pdf\",\n      \"content_type\": \"application/pdf\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Business Registration Certificate\",\n      \"url\": \"https://storage.example.com/docs/business-reg.pdf\",\n      \"content_type\": \"application/pdf\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"payment\": {\n    \"amount\": 500.00,\n    \"currency\": \"USD\",\n    \"transaction_id\": \"{{txn_id}}\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": { "language": "json" }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "customer", "applications"]
            },
            "description": "Covers all 4 customer steps:\n- **Step 1** — `license_type` selects Trade License\n- **Step 2** — `documents` array attaches required files\n- **Step 3** — `payment` settles the fee\n- **Step 4** — endpoint always submits (PENDING → SUBMITTED)\n\nThe pre-request script generates a unique `transaction_id` so this request can be run multiple times without duplicate key errors.\n\nOn success the test script auto-saves `application_id` to `{{app_id}}`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                  { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "CUSTOMER" },
                  { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "customer-001" }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"license_type\": \"TRADE_LICENSE\",\n  \"commodity\": {\"name\": \"General Trading\", \"description\": \"Import/Export\", \"category\": \"Commerce\"},\n  \"documents\": [{\"name\": \"Passport\", \"url\": \"https://storage.example.com/passport.pdf\", \"content_type\": \"application/pdf\"}],\n  \"payment\": {\"amount\": 500.00, \"currency\": \"USD\", \"transaction_id\": \"TXN-EXAMPLE-001\"}\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "customer", "applications"]
                }
              },
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"application_id\": \"a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Bad Request — missing field",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                  { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "CUSTOMER" },
                  { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "customer-001" }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"license_type\": \"\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "customer", "applications"]
                }
              },
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"license_type is required\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List My Applications",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "CUSTOMER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{customer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "customer", "applications"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all applications belonging to the authenticated customer (filtered by X-User-ID)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Application by ID",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('ID matches saved app_id', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('app_id'));",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Has commodity', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().commodity).to.not.be.null);",
                  "pm.test('Has documents', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().documents).to.be.an('array').with.length.greaterThan(0));",
                  "pm.test('Has payment', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().payment).to.not.be.null);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "CUSTOMER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{customer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications/{{app_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "customer", "applications", "{{app_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieves a single application by ID.\nVerifies commodity, documents, and payment are all present (Steps 1–3 view)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel Application (Step 4 — Cancel)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "CUSTOMER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{customer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/customer/applications/{{app_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "customer", "applications", "{{app_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Cancel action. Transitions PENDING → CANCELLED.\n\n⚠️ Only works while status is PENDING. After Submit, the application is in SUBMITTED and this returns 422.\n⚠️ Returns 403 if the X-User-ID does not match the application's applicant_id."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Reviewer",
      "description": "Use Case: Review requested New Application for Trade License.\nAll requests require `X-Role: REVIEWER` and `X-User-ID` headers.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Pending Review Queue (SUBMITTED + REREVIEW)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "// Auto-save first item's ID for quick action testing",
                  "const apps = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (apps.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('app_id', apps[0].id);",
                  "    console.log('Set app_id to first in queue:', apps[0].id, '| status:', apps[0].status);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all SUBMITTED and REREVIEW applications — the full reviewer work queue.\n\nOptionally filter by status:\n- `?status=SUBMITTED` — new submissions only\n- `?status=REREVIEW` — sent back by approver only\n\nThe test script auto-saves the first application's ID to `{{app_id}}`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List Pending Review Queue (SUBMITTED only)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('All items are SUBMITTED', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.json().forEach(app => {",
                  "        pm.expect(app.status).to.eql('SUBMITTED');",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications?status=SUBMITTED",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "SUBMITTED", "description": "Filter to new submissions only" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns only SUBMITTED applications. Use when you want to separate new submissions from rereview items."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Application Detail",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status is SUBMITTED or REREVIEW', () => {",
                  "    const status = pm.response.json().status;",
                  "    pm.expect(['SUBMITTED', 'REREVIEW']).to.include(status);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications/{{app_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications", "{{app_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Steps 1–3 for the reviewer:\n- **Step 1** — View commodity\n- **Step 2** — View attached documents\n- **Step 3** — View settled payment"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Accept (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"ACCEPT\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications/{{app_id}}/action",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications", "{{app_id}}", "action"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Accept action.\nTransitions SUBMITTED | REREVIEW → ACCEPTED, forwarding the application to the approver queue."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Reject (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"REJECT\",\n  \"notes\": \"Passport copy is not legible. Please resubmit a clearer scan.\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications/{{app_id}}/action",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications", "{{app_id}}", "action"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Reject action.\nTransitions SUBMITTED | REREVIEW → REJECTED.\n`notes` is required — returns 400 if omitted."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Adjust (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "REVIEWER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{reviewer_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"ADJUST\",\n  \"notes\": \"Please upload a higher-resolution scan of the trade certificate on page 2.\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/reviewer/applications/{{app_id}}/action",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "reviewer", "applications", "{{app_id}}", "action"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Adjust action.\nTransitions SUBMITTED | REREVIEW → ADJUSTED, flagging the application for correction by the customer.\n`notes` is required — returns 400 if omitted."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Approver",
      "description": "Use Case: Approve Reviewed New Application for Trade License.\nAll requests require `X-Role: APPROVER` and `X-User-ID` headers.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Pending Approval Queue",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "// Auto-save first item's ID for quick action testing",
                  "const apps = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (apps.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('app_id', apps[0].id);",
                  "    console.log('Set app_id to first in queue:', apps[0].id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "APPROVER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{approver_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/approver/applications",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "approver", "applications"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all ACCEPTED applications — the approver's work queue.\n\nThe test script auto-saves the first application's ID to `{{app_id}}`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Application Detail",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Status is ACCEPTED', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ACCEPTED');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Role",    "value": "APPROVER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID", "value": "{{approver_id}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/approver/applications/{{app_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "approver", "applications", "{{app_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Steps 1–3 for the approver:\n- **Step 1** — View reviewed application\n- **Step 2** — View attached required documents\n- **Step 3** — View settled payment"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Approve (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "APPROVER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{approver_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"APPROVE\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/approver/applications/{{app_id}}/action",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "approver", "applications", "{{app_id}}", "action"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Approve action.\nTransitions ACCEPTED → APPROVED. This is the terminal success state for the workflow."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Reject (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "APPROVER" },
              { "key": "X-User-ID",    "value": "{{approver_id}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"REJECT\",\n  \"notes\": \"Application does not comply with municipal zoning regulation 4.2.\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/approver/applications/{{app_id}}/action",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "approver", "applications", "{{app_id}}", "action"]
            },
            "description": "Step 4 — Reject action at the approver stage.\nTransitions ACCEPTED → REJECTED.\n`notes` is required — returns 400 if omitted."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Action — Rereview (Step 4)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 204 No Content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Role",       "value": "APPROVER" },
